[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Adds 6 extra jewelry slots — 2 rings, 2 keepsakes, and 2 amulets — with full stat support, behind a togglable pouch panel in your inventory.[/size]

[size=3][b]Slots[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Six extra slots[/b] — two of each jewelry category. Stats apply just like the vanilla slots, so a fully kitted character has triple the jewelry stat budget.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Storage-only mode[/b] — optional. The extras still hold items but contribute no stat bonuses, if you'd rather use them as overflow than as buffs.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Persistence[/b] — items in extra slots are saved per-character and survive sessions. Stats apply the moment the save finishes loading.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]UI &amp; equip[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Pouch toggle[/b] — show or hide the extra-slots panel with the arrow button in your inventory. The mod remembers your last choice between sessions.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Hidden but active[/b] — collapsing the panel doesn't unequip anything; jewelry hidden in the pouch still grants its bonuses.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Smart equip[/b] — right-clicking a jewelry item checks every available slot (including the extras) before swapping out something you're already wearing.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Controller navigation[/b] — full controller support for the extra-slot panel.[/size]
[/list]

